challengeName: HP IDOL OnDemand Swift 30 Day Debugger
detailedRequirements:
Background

Hewlett Packard has developed a complete solution for bringing extensive data analytics to your app and for augmenting your Big Data solution using JSON-based REST APIs.  This platform is called IDOL OnDemand and at this point is in the Early Access release phase, open for all Innovators to use.

The true power of IDOL OnDemand is evident when you start to combine the APIs. Consume IDOL OnDemand Indexing APIs to index your unstructured data from social media, mobile devices, CMS, Google docs, Dropbox, email, SharePoint or other sources. Once indexed, analyze and augment your content, using IDOL OnDemand APIs such as OCR, Sentiment Analysis, Extract Entity, Face Detection, Barcode Recognition and Text Extraction. Finally, leverage IDOL OnDemand Search APIs to find what you need and shine light on dark data with advanced search options such as Find Similar, Query Text Index, Find Facets, Clusters or Terms.

Check out the latest challenges from HP IDOL OnDemand at http://idolondemand.topcoder.com.

HP IDOL OnDemand Swift 30 Day Debugger

Had a enought Swift yet?  Didn't think so.  HP and [topcoder] are challenging you to take your Swift skills to the next level.  In this challenge you'll need to identify a couple of well-placed bugs in some Swift code and fix them.  The first 200 valid submissions -- with all bugs removed -- will win a $100 prize.  All you have to do is submit your corrected playground file with output.  Here is how to compete:

1.  Download the Swift code attached to this challenge.

2.  Get an IDOL API Key as outlined in the section "Getting Started with HP IDOL OnDemand" below.  Remember to add [topcoder] in the “How did you hear about IDOL OnDemand?” field.

3.  Load the code into an XCode playground.  If you need help getting started with playgrounds, check out Skip Wilson's tutorial.

4.  Update the IDOL API Key with your own. 

5.  Identify and fix the issues the code.  There are 5 bugs in the code.  Note that the code provided should perform an IDOL OnDemand Query Text Index API call on the English Version of Wikipedia using the search term 'Hewlett-Packard'.  You can find out more information about the Query Text Index API call here.

6.  Submit your playground file with your API Key and the working code. Ensure that your code outputs the correct information in the right sidebar for evaluation.

7. (Optional) Tweet - " I'm an #HP IDOL OnDemand Innovator!!! @idolondemand @topcoder #swift #developer "

Getting Started with HP IDOL OnDemand

Before you can use the API’s you’ll need to sign up for an IDOL OnDemand developer account.

Please indicate that you heard about IDOL OnDemand through [topcoder] in the “How did you hear about IDOL OnDemand?” field:

Once your account has been verified you’ll be assigned a developer account and API Key that will allow you to make API calls.   Complete information about available IDOL OnDemand API’s can be found here.

You’ll need to register for a developer account with HP in order to get access to additional Try functionality in the API console.  Use of the APIs is free and restricted to non-commercial use at this time. Commercial use and pricing will be announced in the near future.

Before you compete in an IDOL-related challenge on [topcoder] please create a topcoder-specific key in your IDOL OnDemand Account.  You can do this by Clicking on Account->API Keys from the developer home page.

Simply generate a new key and rename it to “topcoder” as shown above.   This should be the key that you use in [topcoder] challenge completion.  This will also give you visibility to Preview API’s which may not yet be in public release. 

You should be all set!
finalSubmissionGuidelines: Use Xcode 6.1 beta 2 or later. Upload your Playground, written in Swift of course, as your submission.
